byline.original: By JOSEPH GOLDSTEIN and AL BAKER

abstract: Officials investigating murder of Karina Vetrano while she was jogging through Spring Creek Park in Howard Beach, Queens, are struggling to generate leads; DNA thought to be that of assailant has failed to match profiles of known offenders.
lead_paragraph: The most promising initial lead in the killing of Karina Vetrano — DNA evidence quite likely from the assailant — has not helped identify a suspect, a law enforcement official said.
